    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content</head>
      <p>This addition to the 
         <persname>Louis J. Halle, Jr.</persname>Papers consists of ca.
         400 items (2 Hollinger boxes, ca. .5 linear feet), 1963,
         1975-1992, including typescripts of "The Evolution of World
         Politics," "The Fear of Man," "Notes on Time," and "A
         Recollection of Birds"; two typescripts of his book 
         <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The Appreciation of Birds</bibref>; and his
         correspondence with several publishers concerning its
         publication. There is also some printed material concerning
         birds scattered throughout the correspondence files.</p>
      <p>The majority of the correspondence is with the book's
         publisher, The 
         <corpname>Johns Hopkins University Press</corpname>and the
         Director of the Press, 
         <persname>Jack G. Goellner</persname>. Other correspondents in
         the Johns Hopkins folders include: the Danish illustrator 
         <persname>Jens Gregersen</persname>, biologist 
         <persname>John Bonner</persname>(who wrote the foreword), 
         <persname>Herb Bailey</persname>, manuscript editor 
         <persname>Carol Ehrlich</persname>, and 
         <persname>Jim Johnston</persname>, Associate Director.</p>
      <p>In the general correspondence about 
         <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">The Appreciation of Birds</bibref>, 
         <persname>Louis J. Halle, Jr.</persname>has letters with:</p>
      <p><persname>Richard B. McAdoo</persname>( 
         <corpname>Houghton Mifflin Company</corpname>)</p>
      <p><persname>John Bonner</persname>( 
         <corpname>Princeton University</corpname>)</p>
      <p>
        <persname>Shirley A. Briggs</persname>
      </p>
      <p><persname>Alan Brooke</persname>( 
         <corpname>Michael Joseph Ltd.</corpname>)</p>
      <p><persname>Kenneth C. Danforth</persname>( 
         <corpname>National Geographic Society</corpname>)</p>
      <p>
        <persname>Paul Geroudet</persname>
      </p>
      <p>
        <persname>Felton L. Gibbons</persname>
      </p>
      <p><persname>William B. Goodman</persname>( 
         <persname>David R. Godine</persname>)</p>
      <p><persname>Jens Gregersen</persname>(artist &amp;
         illustrator)</p>
      <p><persname>Daniel Halpern</persname>(Antaeus - 
         <corpname>The Ecco Press</corpname>)</p>
      <p><persname>Michael Kenward</persname>( 
         <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">New Scientist</bibref>)</p>
      <p>
        <persname>Lawrence Kilham, M.D.</persname>
      </p>
      <p><persname>Barbara S. Kouts</persname>(Literary Agent)</p>
      <p><persname>Walter H. Lippincott</persname>( 
         <corpname>Princeton University Press</corpname>)</p>
      <p><persname>Murray Milner, Jr.</persname>( 
         <corpname>University of Virginia</corpname>Sociology
         Dept.)</p>
      <p><persname>Charlton Ogburn</persname>(excerpt only, 1985 Nov
         1)</p>
      <p><persname>Austin Olney</persname>( 
         <corpname>Houghton Mifflin Company</corpname>)</p>
      <p><persname>Robb Reavill</persname>( 
         <corpname>Cornell University Press</corpname>)</p>
      <p><persname>S. Dillon Ripley</persname>( 
         <corpname>Smithsonian Institution</corpname>)</p>
      <p><persname>E.F. Rivinus</persname>( 
         <corpname>Smithsonian Institution Press</corpname>)</p>
      <p><persname>Timothy Seldes</persname>( 
